          "number": "14",
          "title": ".ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON REVERSIBILITY",
          "content": "There are no emissions to soil and water during the use stage.\n\nValuable information is Waste glass wool in the module A5 and C will be classified according to the European Waste Codes:\n\n17 06 04 insulation materials other than those mentioned in 17 06 01 and 17 06 03\n\n12. DEMONSTRATION OF VERIFICATION\n\nEN 15804+A1 serves as the core PCR\n\nIndependent verification of the environmental declaration and data according to standard EN ISO 14025:2010\n\nInternal☐ External☒\n\nThird party verifier:\n\nVinçotte nv\n\nRamses Sterckx\n\nJan Olieslagerslaan 35 1800 Vilvoorde Belgium\n\nrsterckx@vincotte.be\n\n13. APPLICATION UNIT\n\nThis table gives information on the applied product and how the reference flow and table with impacts relate to different\n\napplications.\n\nCommercial namesDescriptionReferenceThicknessScalabilityScalabilitySpecs Application Ratio\n\nflow (mm) minimummaximum\n\n(mm) (mm)\n\nHOMETEC® 35 Mineral 1m² 180 25 260 Euroclass A1,Roof: 1 m² 1\n\n3\n\nFRAMETEC® 35 wool,λ 20 kg/m thermal or acoustic insulation for\n\nFRAMETEC® SLAB 350.035 R-value: 5,10flat and inclined roofs\n\n2\n\nACOUSTIC ROLL W/m·K m·K/W Outer walls:\n\nPARTY WALL ROLL MU1 thermal or acoustic insulation of\n\nCAVITY BATT 35 WS <1 the outer and inner wall.\n\nAFR10 Ceilings:\n\nNo facingsuspended ceilings\n\nfloors:\n\nthermal or acoustic insulation for\n\nfloors between floors\n\nRobustness of material\n\nEase of handling (size and(material resistance to\n\nDescription Type of fixing Level of reversibilitySimplicity of disassemblySpeed of disassembly Damage to other elementsComment\n\nweight)\n\ndisassembly)\n\nRoof: Thermal or acousticscrews, bolts and dowelsreversible with lightsimple – no specificvery speedy disassemblyeasy to handle manually, onethe material resists welldisassembly is\n\ninsulation for flat and repairable damage possible but should be done\n\ndismantling tools required workers is usually sufficientduring disassembly\n\ninclined roofs 